abstract: An obscure F.C.C. inquiry hints that it may force cable companies to open their set-top boxes to all video from the Internet.
snippet: An obscure F.C.C. inquiry hints that it may force cable companies to open their set-top boxes to all video from the Internet.
lead_paragraph: Officially, Julius Genachowski had only a terse one-sentence statement about Comcast‘s proposed acquisition of NBC on Monday. It said: “The FCC will carefully examine the proposed merger and will be thorough, fair and fact-based in its review.”

headline.main: F.C.C. May Pry Open the Cable Set-Top Box

abstract: In a sign that Apple is looking at alternative ways for people to play digital music, the company has agreed to acquire Lala, a start-up, a person with knowledge of the deal said.
snippet: In a sign that Apple is looking at alternative ways for people to play digital music, the company has agreed to acquire Lala, a start-up, a person with knowledge of the deal said.
lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO  In the most recent sign that Apple is looking at alternative ways for people to store and play their digital music, the company has agreed to buy Lala, a four-year-old start-up based in Palo Alto, Calif., a person with knowledge of the deal said Friday.

headline.main: Apple Strikes Deal to Buy the Music Start-Up Lala
headline.print_headline: Apple Strikes Deal to Buy The Music Start-Up Lala

abstract: In the most recent sign that Apple is looking at alternative ways for people to store and play digital music, the company is said to be finalizing talks to acquire Lala, a three-year-old start-up.
snippet: In the most recent sign that Apple is looking at alternative ways for people to store and play digital music, the company is said to be finalizing talks to acquire Lala, a three-year-old start-up.
lead_paragraph: In the most recent sign that Apple is looking at alternative ways for people to store and play their digital music, the company is finalizing talks to acquire Lala, a three-year-old start-up based in Palo Alto, Calif., two people with knowledge of the discussions said Friday, The New York Times’s Brad Stone reports from San Francisco.

headline.main: Apple Is Said to Be Close to Buying Music Start-Up
